<body>
    <h1>Task 17 - RAD</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"723273fa39f5" id=3D"Task17-RAD-1.Introduction">1. I=
ntroduction</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"60262b83ea4e" id=3D"Task17-RAD-1.1Purpose">1.1 Purpose</h2>
<p local-id=3D"5e01a23c3a2f">The purpose of this document is to define the =
requirements for designing and implementing a <strong>multi-VPC AWS network=
 architecture across two regions</strong> with proper subnetting and secure=
 connectivity using <strong>VPC Peering</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7d15570d7d10">This document is intended for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1c7bbb5a3b59">DevOps Engineers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"823ccb55082c">Cloud Engineers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"38d5c7e38ea4">Project Evaluators</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"383e206839ec">Students and Interns</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"1e8b0665c4ea" id=3D"Task17-RAD-1.2Scope">1.2 Scope</h2>
<p local-id=3D"87d64c71a83c"><strong>Included in scope:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2b52dad92409">Design of multiple VPCs across regions</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b3971b9e0f66">Advanced subnetting based on host requirements=
</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"057b724584ad">Public and private subnet configuration</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"975c608678ce">Cross-region and intra-region VPC peering</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5ceae37e1cc9">EC2 deployment and connectivity testing</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4dd850914e8b"><strong>Not included:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dbfdaace8396">Application deployment inside EC2</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f860442f1726">CI/CD pipelines</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"da82f8ff0e8a">Advanced monitoring (CloudWatch deep setup)</p=
></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"8719f17c2d72" id=3D"Task17-RAD-1.3Definitions,Acronyms,andA=
bbreviations">1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d=
af26735-607f-4665-afc1-4a889f6f923d" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"677fd9aa588e">Term</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"e24360c65589">Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b50a80c0d4b1">VPC</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8e229b0ab1a5">Virtual Private Cloud</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"64f28a5c0998">CIDR</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"be5687071ba9">Classless Inter-Domain Routing</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4000d0462733">AZ</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6e81071e5cbb">Availability Zone</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0fccab0c5c97">EC2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3e6adee0644b">Elastic Compute Cloud</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8b1062c8cf96">IGW</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b4a4fedebedd">Internet Gateway</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a5ae97ace3ef">SG</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f621f7d2eddc">Security Group</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"31e1ebce9619" id=3D"Task17-RAD-1.4References">1.4 Reference=
s</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2972b2568f5b">AWS VPC Documentation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"26d98e9a0cb2">AWS EC2 Documentation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0764ebb25540">AWS VPC Peering Guide</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"272c4bfc4be4">Networking Fundamentals</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"5634ada9b443" id=3D"Task17-RAD-1.5Overview">1.5 Overview</h=
2>
<p local-id=3D"dbfe66435da2">This document explains:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bec5d441db26">Multi-VPC architecture design</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0fd68898781d">Subnetting strategy</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6b6267cdceb7">Peering configuration</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"62709899fb64">Functional and non-functional requirements</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"edf67076eca1">Risks and assumptions</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"a2080af0b7d9" id=3D"Task17-RAD-2.ProjectOverview">2. Projec=
t Overview</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"bf797fe74794" id=3D"Task17-RAD-2.1ProjectObjectives">2.1 Pr=
oject Objectives</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f54f97f4acc6">Design a scalable multi-VPC architecture</p></=
li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e7756d09e54d">Implement subnetting based on host requirement=
s</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a89d33f8c510">Establish secure communication using VPC peeri=
ng</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c97899e49084">Separate public and private resources</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"faf388c4e032">Validate connectivity using EC2 instances</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"478be42945d8" id=3D"Task17-RAD-2.2BusinessGoals">2.2 Busine=
ss Goals</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4f5c80de4b1d">Improve network isolation and security</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cafe974ac766">Enable multi-region architecture</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1b64b08d1b93">Ensure scalable and structured cloud design</p=
></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a1646b1dbd76">Reduce risk of network conflicts (CIDR overlap=
)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a24823c9cb7d">Allow controlled communication between offices=
</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"4bfc27a68a24" id=3D"Task17-RAD-2.3Background">2.3 Backgroun=
d</h2>
<p local-id=3D"576c78d4d073">ABC Technologies is expanding its infrastructu=
re across multiple locations.</p>
<p local-id=3D"2935ce15fff1">Previously, a single VPC was used, causing:</p=
>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fcd5fb5401a6">Poor scalability</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d5c354b5662d">Lack of isolation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"756f7bb7ef5e">Difficult management</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"8672e00c7bb7">To solve this, a <strong>multi-VPC architectur=
e</strong> is introduced where:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7234c36f0dc3">HQ environments are hosted in <strong>us-east-=
1</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a556c8984583">Branch offices are hosted in <strong>us-east-2=
</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d47a43b170a8">Connectivity is achieved via <strong>VPC Peeri=
ng</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"43e3366bbec8" id=3D"Task17-RAD-2.4Constraints">2.4 Constrai=
nts</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8b262a32cf7d">CIDR ranges must not overlap</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"80cd280b6685">Limited AWS resources (budget/free tier)</p></=
li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"64c922c70ba7">Cross-region latency</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cf8ae88f5392">Manual configuration complexity</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"1bd0de58b375" id=3D"Task17-RAD-3.FunctionalRequirements">3.=
 Functional Requirements</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"c64bb679a24f" id=3D"Task17-RAD-3.1UseCaseDiagram">3.1 Use C=
ase Diagram</h2><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-cente=
r-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedde=
d-image image-center" alt=3D"image-20260322-144652.png" width=3D"468" loadi=
ng=3D"lazy" src=3D"4947ee2e93adff3804cf4df209c1542a3b0ae1cab2938ddb8a914c67=
d294429f" data-image-src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki/download/atta=
chments/1887305922/image-20260322-144652.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDa=
te=3D1774190822066&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"2288" =
data-width=3D"4644" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resourc=
e-id=3D"1885701112" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource=
-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20260322-1=
44652.png" data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-=
resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"18=
87305922" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" data-media-id=3D"df5=
81203-362c-49c3-8fb0-3721d74efb51" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"230">=
</span>
<p local-id=3D"caf65ae4ec14"></p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"a3aec772cb8e" id=3D"Task17-RAD-3.2UseCases">3.2 Use Cases</=
h2>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"b049c9cc26d9" id=3D"Task17-RAD-3.2.1UseCase1:DesignMulti-VP=
CNetwork(CIDR+Subnetting)">3.2.1 Use Case 1: Design Multi-VPC Network (CIDR=
 + Subnetting)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"fdc3204fa2c7"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
DevOps engineer designs VPC CIDR ranges and subnet allocation.</p>
<p local-id=3D"36fa160d5bab"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c26abed9c995">DevOps Engineer</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"91c7525540cd"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"51a3409a7f64">Network requirements defined</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"62d23dda624b"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c74609e8cc80">Non-overlapping CIDR ranges assigned</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"d7106627b49f"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"67018f3f23b6">Analyze host requirements</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9d7c750da655">Assign CIDR blocks to each VPC</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"17168a2b3f13">Divide CIDR into subnets</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9058a0ee1fd6">Ensure no overlap</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"4897ccba986f"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c5e752b1dad2">If overlap occurs =E2=86=92 redesign CIDR</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"810331cf3f7f" id=3D"Task17-RAD-3.2.2UseCase2:ConfigurePubli=
c&amp;PrivateSubnets">3.2.2 Use Case 2: Configure Public &amp; Private Subn=
ets</h3>
<p local-id=3D"6f183d65c642"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
Create subnets based on usage (public/private).</p>
<p local-id=3D"4fd7b2b25829"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0ce2b11c96dc">DevOps Engineer</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f9bad545a7e0"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"801d1df6cf89">VPC created</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"33628182126e"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1048f154383c">Subnets created and categorized</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b8f803322ee5"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b3b0a5bbd2a5">Create public subnet</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"61c54f448d44">Attach route to IGW</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8c700db64abd">Create private subnet</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c5977ca8aa7f">Configure routing (NAT or internal)</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"a60619d78c50"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0e1b336dc564">Misconfigured routing =E2=86=92 no connectivit=
y</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"a14b7e156f0c" id=3D"Task17-RAD-3.2.3UseCase3:SetupVPCPeerin=
g(Cross&amp;IntraRegion)">3.2.3 Use Case 3: Setup VPC Peering (Cross &amp; =
Intra Region)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"0d9af30afc5c"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
Establish connectivity between VPCs.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f4a156f6ce3d"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e5b826e0f419">DevOps Engineer</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"0e5fb0d0e620"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7eb4d3251c31">VPCs exist</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b1250a154bef"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6706d9474f48">VPCs can communicate</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e854470c8acd"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b6ecc6303b12">Create peering request</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b92de85f20a5">Accept peering</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"860eb0190408">Update route tables</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7464e38bf5d0">Verify connectivity</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"44d73d4a726b"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8269252f79e4">Missing route =E2=86=92 communication fails</p=
></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"cd9fc74e1dcc" id=3D"Task17-RAD-3.2.4UseCase4:ConfigureRoute=
Tables&amp;SecurityGroups">3.2.4 Use Case 4: Configure Route Tables &amp; S=
ecurity Groups</h3>
<p local-id=3D"92b91fc11874"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
Control traffic flow and access.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f0b3947183d2"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"180c7b5b9cd9">DevOps Engineer</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1d51acaab4f8"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f1befc88d246">Subnets and VPCs exist</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"76be04f1513f"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"96e5ee70dd01">Secure communication established</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5a8746b52aa7"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"395eeee82d1f">Create route tables</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e59f048934a7">Add routes for peering</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"551946c291cb">Configure security groups</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0237133bbab9">Allow required ports</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"fa5695c0f261"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9d95ed3f5346">Blocked ports =E2=86=92 connection failure</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"1f205584f6c3" id=3D"Task17-RAD-3.2.5UseCase5:DeployEC2&amp;=
TestConnectivity">3.2.5 Use Case 5: Deploy EC2 &amp; Test Connectivity</h3>
<p local-id=3D"fbe925cd2c45"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
Deploy EC2 instances and test communication.</p>
<p local-id=3D"fd5b1ab1f6a6"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1e06cafb2758">DevOps Engineer</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3e46c47ce7d3">Test User</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"690aef4416fe"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"89c2bf811261">Network setup complete</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"6380e6f60bca"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2779acb9a775">Connectivity verified</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"095a75ceb1a3"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6b6781b4c46a">Launch EC2 in public/private subnets</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e62ed4b4280b">Configure security groups</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e0d20a3d9c01">Test using telnet/SSH</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"90689a5234a4">Validate connectivity</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"6bc4813d497c"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d4ffa09b505c">Failed test =E2=86=92 troubleshoot routing/SG<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"e6af46d5ed55" id=3D"Task17-RAD-4.Non-FunctionalRequirements=
">4. Non-Functional Requirements</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"4a79bd8d2346" id=3D"Task17-RAD-4.1PerformanceRequirements">=
4.1 Performance Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b08115a0d13d">Low latency communication within region</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"676b6a7a1989">Acceptable latency across regions</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"98cb056e7d7e">Efficient routing</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"5a7904160a78" id=3D"Task17-RAD-4.2SecurityRequirements">4.2=
 Security Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e90c217beb14">Private subnets not directly accessible</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"81931788d33b">Controlled access via Security Groups</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5b9482e86b44">No public exposure of sensitive resources</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"af8cf33b0274" id=3D"Task17-RAD-4.3UsabilityRequirements">4.=
3 Usability Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"edf2190a2476">Easy-to-understand network design</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9e131b0fee0a">Clear subnet separation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5959ac1c1235">Simple connectivity testing</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"0d6ad46a9adc" id=3D"Task17-RAD-4.4ReliabilityRequirements">=
4.4 Reliability Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c6979b9ae3c0">Multi-region architecture ensures resilience</=
p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b71a5f54d1c3">Isolation between VPCs prevents failures</p></=
li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"39e7131a80eb">Controlled routing improves stability</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"b644b27a416b" id=3D"Task17-RAD-4.5ComplianceRequirements">4=
.5 Compliance Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"19f63b611d33">Follow AWS networking best practices</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"86e7aeb145d4">Secure data transmission</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dc353847f079">Proper access control</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"d8884392a6c1" id=3D"Task17-RAD-5.AssumptionsandDependencies=
">5. Assumptions and Dependencies</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"4c3f345ad3c6" id=3D"Task17-RAD-5.1Assumptions">5.1 Assumpti=
ons</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"899283b6ca46">AWS services are available</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5575f2f22d7f">Internet access exists</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"28514cf6f62a">Proper IAM permissions available</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"15b7e55cb95c" id=3D"Task17-RAD-5.2Dependencies">5.2 Depende=
ncies</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"96114544ad13">AWS VPC service</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"95de37463636">EC2 instances</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7790f6bc999d">Internet Gateway</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e07bb2c47443">VPC Peering</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"b62daef1e1bc" id=3D"Task17-RAD-6.RiskAnalysis">6. Risk Anal=
ysis</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"c4c7b54fa911" id=3D"Task17-RAD-6.1RiskIdentification">6.1 R=
isk Identification</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a83f9f15b2ec">CIDR overlap</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fdd72938e6a8">Incorrect route table configuration</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"710d061a01d8">Security misconfiguration</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9d81725c12eb">Peering misconfiguration</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"c09033546ddd" id=3D"Task17-RAD-6.2RiskMitigation">6.2 Risk =
Mitigation</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"555c6d7b3404">Plan CIDR carefully</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"042081a824cd">Validate routes before deployment</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a30c3fc086f8">Use security group rules properly</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4c45157d9ebd">Test connectivity step-by-step</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
